race.comment: FILA MIA (8) stuck on gamely when sitting on the pace first-up, finishing 1.5L. She went to a new level when out in trip as a 2Y), going under narrowly in the Sires. Looks well placed off the first-up run and if she can improve as anticipated, she'll be very hard to beat. MALAGARASI (5) is a son of Smart Missile on debut for Team Williams. He's shown enough at the trials coming in to suggest he's got some ability, and the 1300m trip looks ideal on debut. Can make an immediate impact. SPELLBORN (7) is another debutant, this time out of the Vahala camp where he ran behind a subsequent debut winner at his latest trial. He maps to get his chance from the draw and if he can run up to his trial performance, he'll be in the finish. DIAMOND WARRIOR (1) is some query off his latest trial, but his form last campaign makes for good reading. Worth including. OLAF THE SNOWMAN (3) was solid first-up from a mile back and is not to be discounted.
